Eight buses set alight in Gqeberha as the dispute between taxi drivers and their bosses drag on. eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports. Courtesy #DStv403 GQEBERHA - An investigation has been launched into the torching of eight passenger buses in GqeberhaÂ in the Eastern Cape. It comes amid a continuing protest by angry taxi operators. They claim their associations have robbed them of Ters funding. Several schools and malls in the metro have had to shut down since the beginning of the protest on Tuesday. Taxi operators in Gqeberha say their protest could continue for the remainder of the week. * eNCA's Ronald Masinda reports.